Class Egg

java.lang.Object
IslandItem
Egg
public class Egg extends IslandItem
Egg class represents an egg on the island.

Eggs must belong to an nest on the island and contains an animal.

    • Egg

      public Egg(int xPosition, int yPosition, Class<? extends Animal> class1)
      Egg constructor method creates a new Egg object.

      Parameters:
      xPosition - stores the x coordinate of the Egg on the island. If the egg is in a nest this should be the same as the xPosition of the nest.
      yPosition - stores the y coordinate of the Egg on the island. If the egg is in a nest this should be the same as the yPosition of the nest.
      class1 - stores the class of the animal in the egg.
